[zero_shot][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][mmlu] sample 30/100 done id=mmlu_validation_440 prediction="The Phillips curve is a graphical representation of the relationship between government spending and tax collections. It is upward sloping from left to right, indicating that as government spending increases, tax collections tend to increase. This relationship is known as the Phillips curve, named after the economist John Maynard Keynes, who first proposed it in 1936.\n\nThe Phillips curve is based on Keynes's theory of the business cycle, which suggests that economic fluctuations are caused by changes in the level of aggregate demand (the total amount of goods and services that people want to buy). When aggregate demand increases, businesses and consumers spend more money, which leads to an increase in tax collections. This increase in tax collections is then used to fund government spending, which increases government spending and tax collections again.\n\nThe Phillips curve is a useful tool for policymakers and economists to understand the relationship between government spending and tax collections. By understanding the relationship between these two variables, policymakers can make informed decisions about how to allocate resources and manage the economy.\n\nIn conclusion, the Phillips curve is a graphical representation of the relationship between government spending" gold='C' correct=False
