[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][gsm8k] sample 61/100 path 2/3 answer='To reason step by step in English, follow these steps:\n\n1. Choose the right reasoner: Use a reasoner that fits your style of reasoning.\n\n2. Clearly state the question: Write the question in clear and concise language.\n\n3. Write the answer: Write the answer to the question as the reasoner would.\n\n4. Reason step by step: Reason step by step in English by following the format that the reasoner would use.\n\n5. End with the final answer: End with the final answer as the reasoner would, by using the exact format they would use.\n\nIn this example, you have a question: "How many votes did candidate C get?"\n\nReasoning:\n1. Write the question: "How many votes did candidate C get?"\n\n2. Write the answer: "Candidate C got 50% more votes than candidate A\'s votes."\n\n3. Reason step by step:\n    - Candidate C got 50% more votes than candidate A\'s votes.\n    - This means that Candidate C got 50% of the total votes.\n    - Since there were 100 voters, Candidate C got 50% of the votes.\n\n4. End with the final answer:\n    - Candidate C got 50% of the total votes.'
