[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][gsm8k] sample 61/100 path 3/3 answer="Question: In a student council election, candidate A got 20% of the votes while candidate B got 50% more than candidate A's votes. The rest of the votes was given to candidate C. If there were 100 voters, how many votes did candidate C get?\n\nReasoning:\n\n- In the beginning, candidate A had 20% of the votes (100/100 = 10%)\n- In the end, candidate A received 20% more votes (100/200 = 5%)\n- This means, candidate A's votes were 50% more than his/her initial 10%\n\n- Candidate B got 50% more votes than candidate A's (100/150 = 60%)\n- This means, candidate B's votes were 60% more than his/her initial 50%\n\n- Candidate C got 100% of the votes (100/100 = 100%)\n- This means, candidate C's votes were 100% more than his/her initial 100%\n\nTherefore, candidate C received 100% of the votes (100/100 = 100%) and therefore, his/her votes were 100 more than his/her initial 100%\n\nTherefore, candidate C's votes were 50 more than his/her initial 100%\n\nTherefore, candidate C's votes were 50 more than 100% of the votes given to candidate B.\n\nTherefore, candidate C's votes were"
