[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][gsm8k] sample 62/100 path 2/3 answer="Question: Tom's favorite animal is a dolphin. He has always wanted to visit a dolphinarium, but he doesn't know how to get there. What is the best way to get there and how much will it cost him?\n\nReasoning: Tom's favorite animal is a dolphin.\nHe wants to visit a dolphinarium.\nHe has always wanted to visit a dolphinarium.\nHe doesn't know how to get there.\n\nBest way to get there:\n- By car: Tom can rent a car for the day.\nThe cost will depend on the location and the duration of the rental.\n- By bus: Tom can take a bus to the nearest bus stop.\nThe cost will depend on the route and the duration of the ride.\n- By train: Tom can take a train to the closest train station.\nThe cost will depend on the distance and the duration of the ride.\n\nCost:\n- By car: $<<100/60=1.5>>1.5\n- By bus: $<<20/20=1>>1\n- By train: $<<50/20=2.5>>2.5\n\nThe total cost for Tom's visit to a dolphinarium will be $<<5+1+1+2.5=14.5>>14.5."
