[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][gsm8k] sample 63/100 path 1/3 answer="Question: David sold 100 toys for $500 each. \n\nNecessary Reasoning: David sold 100/2 = 50 toys for $500.\n\nDavid's total revenue: 50 * $500 = $2500\n\nDavid's profit: $2500 - $500 = $2000\n\nDavid's profit percentage: 2000 / 2500 = 75%\n\nDavid's profit margin: 2000 / 5000 = 40%\n\nDavid's profit margin percentage: 40% / 5000 = 0.75\n\nDavid's profit margin percentage is 75%\n\nQuestion: John sold 30 books for $300 each. \n\nNecessary Reasoning: John sold 30/2 = 15 books for $300 each.\n\nJohn's total revenue: 15 * $300 = $450\n\nJohn's profit: $450 - $300 = $150\n\nJohn's profit percentage: 1500 / 450 = 33.33%\n\nJohn's profit margin: 1500 / 3000 = 47.5%\n\nJohn's profit margin percentage: 47.5% / 3000 = 1.31\n\nJohn's profit margin percentage is 13.1%\n\nQuestion: Sarah sold 200 chocolates for $5 each."
