[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][gsm8k] sample 92/100 path 2/3 answer='Question: Madeline ate 6 grapes. Her brother wanted to make grape juice and used up 5 times as many grapes as Madeline to make a full glass. Their mother then used the remaining grapes to make 4 pies. How many grapes were there at the beginning if the pie recipe calls for 12 grapes per pie?\n\nReasoning: \n\nIn the beginning, there were 12 grapes.\n\n12 grapes x 5 = 60 grapes.\n\n60 grapes + 5 grapes = 65 grapes.\n\n65 grapes + 5 grapes = 70 grapes.\n\n70 grapes + 5 grapes = 75 grapes.\n\n75 grapes + 5 grapes = 80 grapes.\n\n80 grapes + 5 grapes = 85 grapes.\n\n85 grapes + 5 grapes = 90 grapes.\n\n90 grapes + 5 grapes = 95 grapes.\n\n95 grapes + 5 grapes = 100 grapes.\n\nTherefore, there were 100 grapes at the beginning.'
