[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][gsm8k] sample 94/100 path 2/3 answer='Question: The Kennel house keeps 3 German Shepherds and 2 Bulldogs.\n\nIf a German Shepherd consumes 5 kilograms of dog food and a bulldog consumes 3 kilograms of dog food per day, how many kilograms of dog food will they need in a week?\n\nReasoning:\n\n1. German Shepherd consumes 5 kilograms of dog food:\n    - This means that they eat 5/kg (500 grams) of dog food per day.\n    - This is calculated by dividing 5 by 1000 (the gram unit) and multiplying the result by 100 (the kilogram unit).\n    - This gives 5 * 100 / 1000 = 500 grams.\n\n2. Bulldog consumes 3 kilograms of dog food per day:\n    - This means that they eat 3/kg (300 grams) of dog food per day.\n    - This is calculated by dividing 3 by 1000 (the gram unit) and multiplying the result by 100 (the kilogram unit).\n    - This gives 3 * 100 / 1000 = 300 grams.\n\nThis means that the German Shepherd and Bulldog need a total of 500 + 300 = 800 grams of dog food per week.'
