[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][gsm8k] sample 94/100 path 3/3 answer='Question: The Kennel house keeps 3 German Shepherds and 2 Bulldogs. If a German Shepherd consumes 5 kilograms of dog food and a bulldog consumes 3 kilograms of dog food per day, how many kilograms of dog food will they need in a week?\n\nReasoning:\nThe Kennel house keeps 3 German Shepherds and 2 Bulldogs.\n\nA German Shepherd consumes 5 kilograms of dog food per day.\nA Bulldog consumes 3 kilograms of dog food per day.\n\nTherefore, the German Shepherd consumes 5 * 3 = 15 kilograms of dog food per week.\n\nSimilarly, the Bulldog consumes 3 * 3 = 9 kilograms of dog food per week.\n\nTherefore, the total amount of dog food needed in a week by the Kennel house is 15 + 9 = 24 kilograms.'
