[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][gsm8k] sample 95/100 path 1/3 answer='Question: In a family, there are 2 brothers and 3 sisters. All sisters are the same age, which is 16. One of the brothers is 12 years old, which is half the age of the older brother.\n\nReasoning:\n- All siblings are the same age, so the total age of the family is 2 + 2 + 3 + 12 + 16 = 16.\n- The brother who is 12 years old is half the age of the older brother, so the total age of the siblings who are 12 is 3.\n- The total age of the siblings is therefore 16 + 3 = 19.\n- The total age of all siblings is therefore 19.'
