[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][csqa] sample 45/100 path 1/3 answer='Question: By learning about the world, many poor college students gain what?\nChoices:\nA. pleasure\nB. greater mobility\nC. desire to travel\nD. global warming\nE. increased security\n\nReasoning:\n\n1. Poor college students often face financial constraints, making it difficult for them to afford expensive travel or vacations. By learning about the world through study abroad programs or cultural immersion trips, they gain firsthand experience in different cultures and gain a deeper understanding of global issues.\n\n2. By learning about the world, poor college students also gain a sense of global mobility, which can lead to greater personal and professional opportunities. For example, they may be able to travel to other countries and experience firsthand the benefits of international collaboration.\n\n3. Poor college students often face social isolation and lack of mobility due to financial constraints. By learning about the world through study abroad programs or cultural immersion trips, they gain the opportunity to meet and connect with people from different cultures and backgrounds. This can lead to new friendships and opportunities for professional development.\n\n4. Poor college students often face increased security due to their lack of financial resources. By learning about the world through study abroad programs or cultural immersion trips, they gain firsthand experience in situations of conflict and security, which can inform their decision-making and decision-making processes.\n\nIn summary, by learning about the world through study abroad programs or cultural immersion trips, poor college students gain a sense of global mobility, experience firsthand the benefits of international collaboration, and gain the opportunity to meet and connect with people from different cultures and backgrounds.'
