[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][csqa] sample 83/100 path 2/3 answer="To reason step by step in English, follow the format:\n\n1. Determine the topic of the question or instruction.\n2. Identify the main idea or central message of the question or instruction.\n3. Create a series of steps or questions that lead to the main idea.\n4. Use each step or question to answer the question or instruction.\n5. Use a clear and concise writing style, avoiding any unnecessary or extraneous details.\n6. Include a closing sentence that summarizes the main idea or central message.\n\nExamples:\n\nQuestion: The school's sanctions were a punishing blow.\n\nStep 1: Identify the main idea or central message: The school was disciplined for violating student code of conduct.\n\nStep 2: Create a series of questions: 1. What kind of disciplinary action did the school take? 2. Was the school punitive or lenient? 3. Who was the target of the disciplinary action? 4. What was the severity of the punishment?\n\nStep 3: Use each step or question to answer the question or instruction: 1. What kind of disciplinary action did the school take? The school was disciplined for violating student code of conduct. 2. Was the school punitive or lenient? The school punished the target of the disciplinary action. 3. Who was the target of the disciplinary action? The student who violated the student code of conduct. 4. What was the severity of the punishment? The student was suspended for three days.\n\nStep 4: Use a clear and concise writing style, avoiding any unnecessary or extraneous details: The school's disciplinary action was severe enough to suspend the student for three"
