[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][mmlu] sample 25/100 path 2/3 answer='Question: A large positive value for the standard Gibbs free energy change (ΔG°) for a reaction means\nChoices:\nA. the reaction is thermodynamically favored with virtual complete conversion of reactants to products\nB. an extremely fast chemical reaction\nC. a reaction with a very large increase in entropy\nD. none of the above\n\nReasoning:\n1. Thermodynamics: The standard Gibbs free energy change (ΔG°) is a measure of the work done by the system (i.e., heat) to change its state. A large positive ΔG° means that the system undergoes a net energy gain, indicating a favorable reaction.\n2. Reaction: The reaction of interest is a chemical reaction, where a large positive ΔG° indicates that the reaction proceeds at a high rate. This indicates that the reaction is thermodynamically favored with virtual complete conversion of reactants to products.\n3. Entropy: Entropy is a measure of the disorder or randomness of a system. A large increase in entropy indicates that the system is in a highly disordered state, indicating a fast reaction.'
