[self_consistency][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][mmlu] sample 30/100 path 1/3 answer='Question: The Phillips curve\nChoices:\nA. shows how government spending and tax collections are related.\nB. is upward sloping from left to right.\nC. indicates that inflation will be high when unemployment is low.\nD. shows how the equilibrium price level is related to fiscal policy.\n\nReasoning:\nThe Phillips curve is a graphical representation of how changes in government spending and tax collections affect inflation and unemployment. The curve is upward-sloping from left to right, indicating that as government spending increases, inflation also increases, while as government spending decreases, inflation decreases. The equilibrium price level is related to fiscal policy because it is the level of government spending that achieves a stable, balanced, and sustainable level of economic activity. In other words, reducing government spending or increasing taxes can help achieve a more stable, balanced, and sustainable level of economic activity. Therefore, the Phillips curve can be used to predict inflation and unemployment in the economy.'
