x]/(x^2 + c_1) is a field.\n\n5. Therefore, Z_3[x]/(x^2 + c) is a field for all c in Z_3.\n\n6. Since Z_3[x] is a field, it follows that all elements of Z_3 are invertible.\n\n7. Therefore, the statement in the question is true.\n\nQuestion: Statement 1 | If aH is an element of a factor group, then |aH| divides |a|.\n\nReasoning:\n1. Start with the assumption that |a| is not a factor of |aH|.\n\n2. Subtract |a| from both sides of the equation, giving |aH| = |a|.\n\n3. Repeating the previous steps, we get:\n|aH| = |a|\n|a| = |aH|\n|a|': 1, 'A': 1}
